{"id":"project-LICHEN-qccf","title":"codec.rs: compress() falls through to uncompressed for mixed address types","description":"File: rust/lichen-schc/src/codec.rs  
Lines: 841-848 (compress function)

Category: PROTOCOL

The compress function only applies CoAP rules when BOTH addresses are the same type:
```rust
if is_link_local(src) && is_link_local(dst) {
    // Rule 0
} else if is_global(src) && is_global(dst) {
    // Rule 1
}
```

If a packet has mixed addressing (e.g., src=link-local, dst=global, or src=global, dst=link-local), it falls through to uncompressed (rule 255), even though these are valid IPv6 packets that could be handled.

Similarly, ULA addresses (fc00::/7) don't match either is_link_local() or is_global(), so they always fall back to uncompressed.

Impact: 
1. Legitimate IPv6 traffic with mixed address scopes gets no compression
2. ULA (Unique Local Address) networks get no compression benefit
3. Border router traffic (link-local to global) wastes airtime

This may be intentional (rules 0-1 are defined for same-type addressing), but should be documented.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:40:50.813904Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:40:50.813947Z"}

